I didn’t get Beyonce tickets BUT.. 

I tried @juicemadamofficial Turmeric Pom juice and it was 😂😋❤️

Recipe ⬇️

✨ 2 Pomegranates

✨ 5-8 Apples

✨ 1-2 Limes

✨2 inch piece of ginger 

✨3-4 inch piece of turmeric ( don’t forget to sprinkle pepper on it to activate )

✨I ADDED monkfruit just half a teaspoon for some natural sweetener 

🍊 Turmeric : A spice that comes from the root of the curcuma longa plant . Circumin has antioxidants and anti inflammatory properties .

🍎 Pomegranate: May help prevent cancer , boosting digestive health , antioxidant , promotes heart health

Cheers to good health & body loving 👸🏽

🍍 I am a BIG fan of ginger , I put it In mostly all of my juices . After being diagnosed with a bunch of chronic gut issues ginger has helped me with my inflammation & nausea . 

💕Be very careful when adding ginger to your juices , in this batch I actually put WAY too much ginger and had to add monkfruit to sweeten it up 

🫡 I’m also a BIG fan of individuals embracing their bodies & sensuality . If you aren’t that’s okay , just keep scrolling 💕

Why do people juice ? 🍑🍍

😅 Well first it’s just a nice healthy habit to have so ….why not lol 

🍍 Juicing is a great way to give your digestive system a break , all while consuming your nutrients and vitamins to decrease inflammation .

👸🏽For some people juicing is an easier alternative for you to get your fruit and veggie intake up if it’s not easy for you to eat them the standard way .

🥒 It can reset your body and increase your energy 

💕If you are wanting to start your juice journey all juicers are the first step in the right direction but if you can look for a COLD PRESSED juicer . I’ll explain the difference in the comments !

FA meal prep for my 2 day transcon trip ✈️

🌸 TRANSCON 2 DAY = Work one leg ( flight )  to LAX , layover ( mine was 10 hours ) , work one leg ( flight ) back to JFK and I’m done 

💞 I do understand that with my seniority it is easier for me to work these ideal transcon trips oppose to someone that just graduated . HOWEVER in NYC baby , just work OT and you can make schedule magic happen 😂

💖 My airline all planes have ovens we can use 

💗 My report ( clock in time) was 4pm , with a release ( clock out time ) of 6 pm the next day . This allowed me to keep majority of my routine during the day before going to work 

💕 My lunchbox is from @travelprointl and I put all my food into the bigger lunch box at the end 😂
